---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="studio — jka">
  <section class="studio-hero">
    <img src="/studio/founders.jpg" alt="jihad khairallah and nadeen roufael, founders of jka, before a kōzō wall" />
  </section>

  <p class="studio-credit">jihad khairallah, architecture and interior architecture<br>nadeen roufael, interior architecture and furniture</p>

  <div class="studio-hero-gap"></div>

  <section class="studio-statement">
    <p class="studio-statement-text">we look for a long time, then remove what was never needed. what remains is precise, and natural light is given room to define the space.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="silence-threshold"></div>
  <section class="studio-section settle">
    <div><span class="tag-index">a</span><span class="tag-name">holistic<br>authorship</span></div>
    <p class="section-copy">we do not draw an envelope and hand the interior to other hands. each commission is one continuous work. the topography of the site sets the datum, the structural grid orders the plan, the openings are cut to bring light in as a material, and the same logic carries down to the interior architecture and to the edge of a single cabinet door. a space is read whole, in one movement, not divided among trades. the furniture is not placed in the room, it is drawn out of the geometry that made the room. this is the difference between fitting out a building and authoring one. the work is finished when nothing further can be removed.</p>
  </section>
  <div class="studio-hairline"></div>
  <section class="studio-section settle">
    <div><span class="tag-index">b</span><span class="tag-name">provenance<br>&amp; longevity</span></div>
    <p class="section-copy">jka was established in beirut in 1998. close to three decades of built work, in lebanon, the levant, and the gulf, have given what no portfolio can show on its own, judgement, earned on difficult sites, in hard climates, against the standards of private clients across the region. beirut taught us to work under constraint. the gulf asked for the same discipline at scale. longevity here is not a line on a letterhead. it is the quiet behind every drawing, the knowledge that the condition has been seen before, detailed before, resolved before, and that we know, without hesitation, what does not belong in the answer.</p>
  </section>
  <div class="silence-major"></div>
  <section class="studio-grid settle">
    <div>
      <div class="col-head first">practice</div>
      <div class="grid-item">architecture</div>
      <div class="grid-item">interior architecture</div>
      <div class="grid-item">bespoke product design</div>
      <div class="col-head">selected recognition</div>
      <div class="grid-item dim">award-winning product design</div>
      <div class="grid-item dim">press, forthcoming</div>
    </div>
    <div class="meta-block">
      <b>enquiries</b>mail@jihadk.com<br><br>
      <b>parameters</b>private houses, workplaces, and retail, in lebanon, the gulf, and beyond. we take few projects and stay close to each one. the work begins with a conversation, before there is a brief.<br><br>
      <b>studio</b>riverside 2404, sin el fil, beirut · est. 1998
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="silence-module"></div>
  <a class="commission-line" href="/projects"><span>view all projects</span><span>→</span></a>
  <footer class="site-footer">
    <a class="brand-logo-link" href="/" aria-label="jka — home">
      <img src="/jka-monogram.png" alt="jka" class="brand-logo footer" />
    </a>
    <a class="trace" href="mailto:mail@jihadk.com">mail@jihadk.com</a>
    <nav class="footer-social" aria-label="social links">
      <a href="https://instagram.com/jihadkhairallaharchitects" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="instagram">
        <img src="/icon-instagram.png" alt="" class="social-icon" />
      </a>
      <a href="https://facebook.com/jihadkhairallaharchitects" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="facebook">
        <img src="/icon-facebook.png" alt="" class="social-icon" />
      </a>
      <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jihadkhairallah" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="linkedin">
        <img src="/icon-linkedin.png" alt="" class="social-icon" />
      </a>
    </nav>
    <span class="trace copyright">&copy; 1998-<span class="year">{new Date().getFullYear()}</span> by jihad khairallah architects</span>
  </footer>

  <style>
    /* founders hero */
    .studio-hero { width: 100%; height: 100vh; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
    .studio-hero img {
      position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover; object-position: center 42%;
    }
    .studio-hero-gap { height: clamp(24px, 5vh, 56px); }  /* statement sits close to the hero */

    /* founders credit — quiet hairline caption beneath the portrait */
    .studio-credit {
      margin: clamp(16px, 2.4vh, 26px) auto 0;
      text-align: center;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(11px, 1vw, 13px);
      line-height: 1.75;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }

    /* statement — centred, matched to the landing manifesto size; wraps to two lines if needed */
    .studio-statement { padding: 0 var(--inset); text-align: center; }
    .studio-statement-text {
      margin: 0 auto; text-align: center;
      color: var(--ink-soft); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.5;
      font-size: clamp(13px, 1.7vw, 24px);   /* same as the landing statement */
      max-width: min(74ch, 90vw);            /* breaks the longer line to ~two, always centred */
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .studio-hero { height: auto; aspect-ratio: 3 / 2; }   /* show the whole portrait on phones */
    }
  </style>
</Base>